    public class PairRule<A>

    A descriptor pair rule. This rule defines that like descriptor pairs have priority over unlike descriptor pairs.

        public PairRule(DescriptorAccessor<A> accessor)

    • Method Detail

      • generate

        protected java.util.NavigableSet<DescriptorList> generate(Ligand<A> ligand)
        Generates a set of descriptor lists that maintain the like/unlike pairing whilst descriptors are added. The set is navigable and maintains priority ordering when multiple lists are present. This method is a wrapper for adding the seeding ligand to the queue.
        Parameters:
        ligand - the ligand on which to generate the descriptor lists for
        Returns:
        navigable set of descriptor lists
